The largest warship ever built in the UK has been successfully floated on the water for the first time. 

The 65,000-tonne Royal Navy aircraft carrier HMS Queen Elizabeth was floated out of the docks at Rosyth shipyard, where she was assembled, into the waters of the Forth of Firth in Scotland.

The carrier was formally named by the Queen earlier this month in a ceremony at the Rosyth Dockyard in Fife, where she was assembled and fitted out.

